<h2>Food Truck Design Process</h2>
<p class="body-text"><strong>Step 1: Consultation &amp; Photography</strong> — We photograph your truck from every angle and take precise measurements of every panel, window, vent, and equipment mount. This creates an exact-scale digital template.</p>
<p class="body-text"><strong>Step 2: Design Concepts</strong> — Our designers create 2–3 initial concepts incorporating your logo, brand colors, menu highlights, social media handles, and contact information. We show photorealistic mockups from every angle.</p>
<p class="body-text"><strong>Step 3: Revisions &amp; Approval</strong> — Unlimited revisions until you're 100% satisfied. We ensure the design works at speed (highway visibility), at rest (event lines), and on social media (Instagram-worthy).</p>
<p class="body-text"><strong>Step 4: Print &amp; Install</strong> — HP Latex 800W wide-format printing for vivid, food-safe colors. FDA-compliant overlaminate. Heat-resistant adhesive for kitchen-adjacent surfaces. 3–5 day installation.</p>
<h2>FDA-Compliant Materials</h2>
<p class="body-text">All food truck wraps use materials specifically selected for food service environments:</p>
<ul class="services">
<li><em>FDA-Compliant Overlaminate</em> — Food-safe protective layer that won't contaminate food contact areas.</li>
<li><em>Heat-Resistant Adhesive</em> — Rated for surfaces near grills, fryers, and ovens up to 250°F.</li>
<li><em>Grease-Resistant Finish</em> — Overlaminate protects against grease splatter, steam, and cooking oils.</li>
<li><em>Easy-Clean Surface</em> — Smooth overlaminate allows daily cleaning without damaging the wrap.</li>
<li><em>UV-Resistant Ink</em> — HP Latex inks resist fading from sun exposure at outdoor events.</li>
<li><strong>Commercial-Grade Vinyl</strong> — Avery Dennison MPI 1105 or 3M IJ180-CV3 cast vinyl rated 5–7 years outdoor.</li>
</ul>
