<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>How much does a food truck wrap cost in Chicago?</h3><p>Full wraps range from $4,200–$8,000 depending on size and design complexity. Partial wraps start at $1,500. Menu boards start at $400. All pricing includes custom design, premium materials, and professional installation.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>Are food truck wraps food-safe?</h3><p>Yes. All wraps use FDA-compliant, food-safe overlaminate. Heat-resistant adhesive is used for surfaces near grills, fryers, and steam — ensuring the wrap stays intact and doesn't contaminate food contact areas.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>How long does a food truck wrap last?</h3><p>Premium cast vinyl is rated for 5–7 years outdoor. The overlaminate protects against grease, steam, and UV. Regular cleaning extends wrap life. Most food truck owners refresh their wraps every 3–5 years to update menus and branding.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>Can you wrap around serving windows and equipment?</h3><p>Yes. We template every food truck individually for serving windows, exhaust vents, generators, propane tanks, and equipment. Precision-cut for a seamless, professional finish.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>Do you design food truck wraps?</h3><p>Yes. Our design team specializes in food truck graphics. We create exact-scale templates, photorealistic mockups, and designs that work at highway speed, in event lines, and on social media.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>How long does installation take?</h3><p>Most food truck wraps take 3–5 business days. We accommodate rush timelines for festival season or grand openings — contact us for expedited service.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>Can I update my menu boards without rewrapping the whole truck?</h3><p>Yes. Menu board panels are designed as replaceable sections. Individual panel replacements start at $200–$400 and take 1 day.</p></div>
